Koketso Makola was reported missing on 28 April. And on Sunday, his decomposing body was found with missing body parts. Limpopo cops spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the mutilated body of the 20-year-old was found by a passer-by next to Madibong village. Ngoepe said cops in Sekhukhune outside Groblesdal were notified and reacted swiftly and started with their initial investigations at the crime scene. Ngoepe said the motive behind this killing is still unknown but ritual related may not be ruled out. He said this discovery follows the search operation which was launched for the deceased who went missing since 28 April 2018 at about 20:30 when he went to sleep. The cops joined by the Local community members have searched for the victim everywhere without success. Ngoepe said the cops have opened a case of murder but the suspects are unknown and there is no arrest yet. Anyone with information that can assist the Police in arresting the suspects involved in this matter, may contact Lieutenant Colonel Lesiba Phalane at 082 414 2663 or the crime stop number 0860010111 or the crimeÂ  line sms 32211 or the nearest Police Station. 